editor who oversaw the AP story.

33:35.079 --> 33:36.614 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ms. Wilson, thanks for joining
us.

33:36.647 --> 33:40.718 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How did you come upon the
investigations that
were under way by the U.N.?

33:40.752 --> 33:44.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TRISH WILSON, Associated Press:
Well, earlier
last year, there was a lot of
reporting out

33:44.122 --> 33:49.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the Congo and the Central
African Republic
about another wave of
allegations against

33:49.360 --> 33:55.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.N. peacekeepers, so we decided
to take a
look at the numbers going back
to 2004, when

33:55.099 --> 33:58.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
